  "prompt": "When entering the US will I be detained for a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have a bench warrant issued against you, attempting to enter the United States could potentially lead to detention or other legal complications. U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) officers have the authority to check various databases for outstanding warrants or legal issues when individuals attempt to enter the country. If a warrant is found, it may result in your detention and referral to the appropriate legal authorities.\n\nIt's highly recommended that you consult with a qualified immigration attorney or legal professional before making any travel plans. They can provide you with specific advice based on your situation and help you understand the potential consequences and available options.",
